aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 172 Military Operators
Ecuador operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Ecuadorian Air Force operates 8 Cessna 172F aircraft.
Ecuadorian Army operates 1 Cessna 172G aircraft.
Guatemala operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Guatemalan Air Force operates 6 Cessna 172K aircraft.
Honduras operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Honduran Air Force operates 3 Cessna 172 aircraft.
Indonesia operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Indonesian Air Force Academy operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Iraq operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Iraqi Air Force operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Ireland operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Irish Air Corps operates 8 FR172H aircraft.
Irish Air Corps operates 1 FR172K aircraft.
Five FR172H remained in Irish Air Corps service until 2019.
Liberia operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Air Reconnaissance Unit of Liberia operates 2 Cessna 172 aircraft.
Lithuania operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Lithuanian Air Force operates 1 Cessna 172 aircraft.
Madagascar operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Malagasy Air Force operates 4 Cessna 172M aircraft.
Nicaragua operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Nicaraguan Air Force operates 7 Cessna 172 aircraft.
Pakistan operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Pakistan Air Force operates 4 Cessna 172N aircraft.
Philippines operates Cessna 172 aircraft.
Philippine Army operates 3 units of Cessna 172M aircraft.
The Philippine Army Cessna 172M aircraft are designated PA-101, PA-103, and PA-911.
Philippine Navy operates 1 Cessna 172F aircraft.
The Philippine Navy Cessna 172F is designated as PN 330.
Olympic Aviation donated the Cessna 172F to the Philippine Navy in 2007.
